Ask HN: How can I work less?
text:
I leetcoded to get a big boy job and now I’m paying the price.

My team runs lean and the work is complicated. As a result, I’ve been working long hours and supplementing my days with stimulants to maintain interest and focus to keep up.

Not only do I end each day with extreme exhaustion, but I do this in a cyclic fashion each day leading to cycles of apathy, depression and excitement. Problematically, I now live like this habitually and sort of forgot how to be a human.

I need to figure out how to feel comfortable working less in ways that don’t mentally feel like it’s impacting my work while also figuring out how to live my life outside of a screen.

Additionally, this makes me very boring at parties.

text:

But maybe web technologies have advanced recently so that that’s no longer the case.
